list.name: Default
list.comment: Added export action for saving image

task.summary: Default task
Subclasses QWidget and draws a line given by graphviz
Added a common file with common functions
Uses GraphWidget, adds instance widgets to graphs, uses graphviz to lay out components and connections, and successfully shows something on the screen
Able to handle scientific notation numbers
Added a component window to display component info in a new window, and in the future as a side panel item.
Changed the way ui is refreshed. Ability to get a signal from Instance_Widget to open a component_window. Component_window stored in GraphController
Changed Controller to be a Main window DockWidget is just a decorder of another widget, so creating a dock_widget, and adding a component_widget inside.
Changed controller to create a dock widget every time a component window is created. Component Window does not need mouse event anymore.
More feature/idea
Added checkbox's for hardware and control. Still no where near final design. But it has the templete ready for any design
Connection widget is now a graphics item, added it to the scene. Unnecessary to "draw_background" (i.e hack removed)
Changed instance widget slot so that it doesn't need to give mouse event.

Changed connection_widget to match more like: http://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qtwidgets-graphicsview-elasticnodes-example.html . Made connection_widget "self-contained" in that it draws within its own painter class, and it can set up its bounding box, etc. Interesting how it still need it's parent co-ordinates to satisfy this.
Rename render() to graph_render due to api clashing
Changed to ASTModel, all ast helper functions should be here
Fixed issue when re-syncing model with view (new widget was not successfully found in list when it was supposed to)
Created an update_ui function, which will be called every time a new instance_object is assigned
Attempted moving position, but failed.
Attempted moving position, but failed.

Changed Instance widget to subclass QGraphicsWidget. Involves using LinearLayout (as VBoxLayout isn't available in the QGraphics word). And using proxy_widget as a placeholder (since design is no where near final anyway)
Updated GraphWidget to handle change of subclass in InstanceWidget
Updated GraphController to handle change of subclass in InstanceWidget
Detecting if the widget has been moved by hand (and hence is being pinned to a chosen location)
Created functions to remove instances and all connections
Added "pointers" to source and destination instances, as well as logic to check if edge was given (and if so, create a path)

Added code to create connection widgets. Right now, it creates duplicate connection widget. Will be used for testing. Attempted to code a force-directed / spring graph layout system instead of using graphviz. Unforuntately it failed. Its not stable, due to the algorithm and will require a lot of fiddling with. May come back to this later (hence the inclusion of the code)
Added function to find component
Added Event, Procedure and Dataport "#defines"

Made Instance Widget and Connection Widget independent of the AST Model. Widgets now store all the important information. Instance and Connection represent the graph. Graph_controller has functions to sync the instance with the Lifted_AST.
Moved Create_connection_widget
Added Source interface name information. Connection adds itself in the instance_widgets
Added logic to add a connection.
Added logic to remove a connection.
DockWidget defaults to undocked.
Logic to draw the information manually. Includes C for control, H for hardware

Added support for drawing edges manually * Instance Widget calculates the starting position and ending position of each connection (and calculates angles when there is a clash) * Connection Widget draws the straight or curved line (depending on angle) between two edges. It also has a static method which will draw the connection type. Plan is to subclass the connection depending on the connection type. * Commented out old edge algorithm given by graphviz
Made connections lie below instance widgets

Graph_controller: Support creating Connection Widget specific to the type Connection_widget: draw icons for different connection types. Pen thicker. "Angle" now mean distance between control point and straight line between source and destination. Code will be made clearer later. Instance_widget: changed to choose a "angle" (as per the new definition). Chooses angle better
Graph_widget: Added the ability to zoom in and out by scaling view Instance_widget: emits when instance has moved
Moved all graphing logic to graph widget. Logic for saving, auto layout and zooming
Using geometry function to get the bottom corner Since file menu is added, need to offset the buttons by 20, 40 instead of 20,20. This is due to a weird behaviour with file menus.
Division by zero error possible. Removed bug

Found bug in change_vector_length - where it would crash if it attempted to change the length of a zero vector Moved initialisation of position and angle since it is accessed by instance widgets later on. Created a delete function to delete itself from the source and destination Removed unnecessary pydotplus import I though QtPoint.dotProduct was a static function. Turns out it isn't in python (or maybe it is, but pycharm just likes to complain). Changed it anyway.
When a connection is added to an Instance Widget, the widget will immediately give back a start position for the connection

I learned that you cannot delete objects in a list while iterating through a list. Fixed bugs for those. If attempting to save an image from an unopened ast, save image will not attempt to save anything.
Added ability to open a CAmkES File from a file menu.
Completed two simple TODO's and added a new one
Removed completed TODOs
Set Window Title to either "CAmkES Visualisation Tool" or the file name
